definitions.definition: A high point or position, literally (as, an elevated place; a superior region; a height; the sky; heaven) or figuratively (as, a point of success or achievement; a time when things are at their best, greatest, most numerous, maximum , etc).
examples: It was one of the highs of his career.

subdefinitions.definition: The maximum atmospheric temperature recorded at a particular location, especially during one 24-hour period.

definitions.definition: A period of euphoria , from excitement or from an intake of drugs .
examples: That pill gave me a high for a few hours, before I had a comedown .

definitions.definition: A drug that gives such a high.
A large area of elevated atmospheric pressure; an anticyclone .
examples: A large high is centred on the Azores.

definitions.definition: The highest card dealt or drawn .
